{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"What if our plants"},{"time":2760,"text":"could sense the toxicity\nlevels in the soil"},{"time":5480,"text":"and express that toxicity\nthrough the color of its leaves?"},{"time":9680,"text":"What if those plants could also\nremove those toxins from the soil?"},{"time":14560,"text":"Instead, what if those plants"},{"time":16680,"text":"grew their own packaging,"},{"time":18560,"text":"or were designed to only be harvested"},{"time":21160,"text":"by their owners' own patented machines?"},{"time":23440,"text":"What happens when biological design"},{"time":25360,"text":"is driven by the motivations\nof mass-produced commodities?"},{"time":28920,"text":"What kind of world would that be?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":31240,"text":"My name is Ani, and I'm a designer\nand researcher at MIT Media Lab,"},{"time":35280,"text":"where I'm part of a relatively new\nand unique group called Design Fiction,"},{"time":39440,"text":"where we're wedged somewhere\nbetween science fiction and science fact."},{"time":43560,"text":"And at MIT, I am lucky enough\nto rub shoulders with scientists"},{"time":47720,"text":"studying all kinds of cutting edge fields"},{"time":49720,"text":"like synthetic neurobiology,"},{"time":52120,"text":"artificial intelligence, artificial life"},{"time":54160,"text":"and everything in between."},{"time":55920,"text":"And across campus,\nthere's truly brilliant scientists"},{"time":59760,"text":"asking questions like,\n\"How can I make the world a better place?\""},{"time":63280,"text":"And part of what my group\nlikes to ask is, \"What is better?\""},{"time":66200,"text":"What is better for you, for me,"},{"time":68320,"text":"for a white woman, a gay man,"},{"time":70480,"text":"a veteran, a child with a prosthetic?"},{"time":73000,"text":"Technology is never neutral."},{"time":75080,"text":"It frames a reality"},{"time":76760,"text":"and reflects a context."},{"time":78560,"text":"Can you imagine what it would say\nabout the work-life balance at your office"},{"time":82320,"text":"if these were standard issue\non the first day?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":84520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":85960,"text":"I believe it's the role\nof artists and designers"},{"time":88240,"text":"to raise critical questions."},{"time":90400,"text":"Art is how you can see\nand feel the future,"},{"time":92840,"text":"and today is an exciting\ntime to be a designer,"},{"time":95320,"text":"for all the new tools becoming accessible."},{"time":97480,"text":"For instance, synthetic biology"},{"time":99080,"text":"seeks to write biology\nas a design problem."},{"time":102000,"text":"And through these developments,"},{"time":103560,"text":"my lab asks, what are the roles\nand responsibilities"},{"time":106520,"text":"of an artist, designer,\nscientist or businessman?"},{"time":110880,"text":"What are the implications"},{"time":112440,"text":"of synthetic biology, genetic engineering,"},{"time":115200,"text":"and how are they shaping our notions\nof what it means to be a human?"},{"time":119840,"text":"What are the implications of this\non society, on evolution"},{"time":123160,"text":"and what are the stakes in this game?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":125760,"text":"My own speculative design research\nat the current moment"},{"time":129000,"text":"plays with synthetic biology,"},{"time":130440,"text":"but for more emotionally driven output."},{"time":133480,"text":"I'm obsessed with olfaction\nas a design space,"},{"time":136280,"text":"and this project started with this idea"},{"time":139120,"text":"of what if you could take\na smell selfie, a smelfie?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":142920,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":144400,"text":"What if you could take\nyour own natural body odor"},{"time":147160,"text":"and send it to a lover?"},{"time":149240,"text":"Funny enough, I found that this\nwas a 19th century Austrian tradition,"},{"time":153040,"text":"where couples in courtship\nwould keep a slice of apple"},{"time":155680,"text":"crammed under their armpit during dances,"},{"time":158280,"text":"and at the end of the evening,"},{"time":159840,"text":"the girl would give the guy\nshe most fancied her used fruit,"},{"time":163240,"text":"and if the feeling was mutual,"},{"time":165440,"text":"he would wolf down that stinky apple."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167400,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":171680,"text":"Famously, Napoleon wrote\nmany love letters to Josephine,"},{"time":175000,"text":"but perhaps amongst the most memorable\nis this brief and urgent note:"},{"time":179280,"text":"\"Home in three days. Don't bathe.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":181520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":183600,"text":"Both Napoleon and Josephine\nadored violets."},{"time":187320,"text":"Josephine wore violet-scented perfume,"},{"time":189480,"text":"carried violets on their wedding day,"},{"time":191320,"text":"and Napoleon sent her a bouquet of violets"},{"time":193359,"text":"every year on their anniversary."},{"time":194920,"text":"When Josephine passed away,"},{"time":196520,"text":"he planted violets at her grave,"},{"time":198120,"text":"and just before his exile,"},{"time":199960,"text":"he went back to that tomb site,"},{"time":202120,"text":"picked some of those flowers,\nentombed them in a locket"},{"time":204800,"text":"and wore them until the day he died."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206560,"text":"And I found this so moving,"},{"time":208120,"text":"I thought, could I engineer that violet\nto smell just like Josephine?"},{"time":212040,"text":"What if, for the rest of eternity,"},{"time":213720,"text":"when you went to visit her site,"},{"time":215320,"text":"you could smell Josephine\njust as Napoleon loved her?"},{"time":218600,"text":"Could we engineer new ways of mourning,"},{"time":221040,"text":"new rituals for remembering?"},{"time":223160,"text":"After all, we've engineered\ntransgenic crops"},{"time":225880,"text":"to be maximized for profit,"},{"time":228040,"text":"crops that stand up to transport,"},{"time":230200,"text":"crops that have a long shelf life,"},{"time":232160,"text":"crops that taste sugary sweet\nbut resist pests,"},{"time":234640,"text":"sometimes at the expense\nof nutritional value."},{"time":238080,"text":"Can we harness these same technologies\nfor an emotionally sensitive output?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":242680,"text":"So currently in my lab,"},{"time":244000,"text":"I'm researching questions like,\nwhat makes a human smell like a human?"},{"time":247320,"text":"And it turns out it's fairly complicated."},{"time":249960,"text":"Factors such as your diet,\nyour medications, your lifestyle"},{"time":253200,"text":"all factor into the way you smell."},{"time":255240,"text":"And I found that our sweat\nis mostly odorless,"},{"time":257800,"text":"but it's our bacteria and microbiome"},{"time":259959,"text":"that's responsible for your smells,\nyour mood, your identity"},{"time":263720,"text":"and so much beyond."},{"time":265360,"text":"And there's all kinds\nof molecules that you emit"},{"time":267680,"text":"but which we only perceive subconsciously."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271120,"text":"So I've been cataloging and collecting"},{"time":273480,"text":"bacteria from different sites of my body."},{"time":275680,"text":"After talking to a scientist, we thought,"},{"time":277680,"text":"maybe the perfect concoction of Ani"},{"time":279400,"text":"is like 10 percent collarbone,\n30 percent underarm,"},{"time":283400,"text":"40 percent bikini line and so forth,"},{"time":285720,"text":"and occasionally\nI let researchers from other labs"},{"time":288800,"text":"take a sniff of my samples."},{"time":290480,"text":"And it's been interesting to hear\nhow smell of the body"},{"time":293680,"text":"is perceived outside\nof the context of the body."},{"time":296520,"text":"I've gotten feedback such as,"},{"time":298120,"text":"smells like flowers, like chicken,"},{"time":300600,"text":"like cornflakes,"},{"time":301840,"text":"like beef carnitas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303320,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":305240,"text":"At the same time, I cultivate\na set of carnivorous plants"},{"time":308880,"text":"for their ability to emit\nfleshlike odors to attract prey,"},{"time":312560,"text":"in an attempt to kind of create\nthis symbiotic relationship"},{"time":315400,"text":"between my bacteria and this organism."},{"time":319520,"text":"And as it so happens,\nI'm at MIT and I'm in a bar,"},{"time":322200,"text":"and I was talking to a scientist"},{"time":324520,"text":"who happens to be a chemist\nand a plant scientist,"},{"time":326920,"text":"and I was telling him about my project,"},{"time":328840,"text":"and he was like, \"Well, this sounds\nlike botany for lonely women.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":332000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":335040,"text":"Unperturbed, I said, \"OK.\""},{"time":337960,"text":"I challenged him."},{"time":339200,"text":"\"Can we engineer a plant\nthat can love me back?\""},{"time":342520,"text":"And for some reason,\nhe was like, \"Sure, why not?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":346000,"text":"So we started with,\ncan we get a plant to grow towards me"},{"time":348960,"text":"like I was the sun?"},{"time":350440,"text":"And so we're looking at mechanisms\nin plants such as phototropism,"},{"time":354400,"text":"which causes the plant\nto grow towards the sun"},{"time":356600,"text":"by producing hormones like auxin,"},{"time":358600,"text":"which causes cell elongation\non the shady side."},{"time":361280,"text":"And right now I'm creating\na set of lipsticks"},{"time":363440,"text":"that are infused with these chemicals"},{"time":365280,"text":"that allow me to interact with a plant\non its own chemical signatures --"},{"time":368960,"text":"lipsticks that cause plants\nto grow where I kiss it,"},{"time":372400,"text":"plants that blossom\nwhere I kiss the bloom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375160,"text":"And through these projects,"},{"time":377960,"text":"I'm asking questions like,"},{"time":379400,"text":"how do we define nature?"},{"time":381120,"text":"How do we define nature\nwhen we can reengineer its properties,"},{"time":384680,"text":"and when should we do it?"},{"time":386120,"text":"Should we do it for profit, for utility?"},{"time":389840,"text":"Can we do it for emotional ends?"},{"time":391560,"text":"Can biotechnology be used\nto create work as moving as music?"},{"time":395160,"text":"What are the thresholds between science"},{"time":397080,"text":"and its ability to shape\nour emotional landscape?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":400640,"text":"It's a famous design mantra\nthat form follows function."},{"time":404440,"text":"Well, now, wedged somewhere\nbetween science, design and art"},{"time":408520,"text":"I get to ask,"},{"time":409760,"text":"what if fiction informs fact?"},{"time":411240,"text":"What kind of R&amp;D lab would that look like"},{"time":413320,"text":"and what kind of questions\nwould we ask together?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":415960,"text":"We often look to technology as the answer,"},{"time":418320,"text":"but as an artist and designer,"},{"time":419880,"text":"I like to ask, but what is the question?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":422400,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423640,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}